 Collection Review Committee of Preston Library is responsible for the selection of serial titles  The Committee meets on an ad hoc basis to review requests for serial titles and requests for other materials  Criteria for selection will include the following  The title must support the curricula of the Institute  The reputation of the title and its publisher must be sound  The subscription cost must be justifiable  The title must be indexed in abstracts and or indexes held or accessible to the Institute  Other factors to be considered include  How frequently is the title likely to be used at the Institute  How many requestors have endorsed the selection of the title  How well does the existing serial collection at the Institute cover the subject  How frequently has the title been requested via interlibrary loan  What is the frequency with which the title is cited in the professional literature  Procedures for Selection of Serial Titles The requestor fills out the Serials Subscription Request Form and returns it to the library  The library completes the form  The form is sent to the Department Head of the requesting department for approval  The form is returned to the library  The Collection Review Committee considers the request  The Department Head is notified of the decision regarding the request  If approved by the Committee  the Head of Technical Services will initiate procedures to begin a subscription to the title  Typically  subscriptions will commence with the first issue of the next calendar year or the first issue of the upcoming volume  Please return completed form to the Head of Technical Services  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciati